    <stitle>7.3 Liter Diesel Engine Diagnostics (1991) - "SOLID STATE" GLOW PLUG ANALYSIS GUIDE - "SOLID STATE" GLOW
        PLUG SYSTEM REPLACEMENT PROCEDURES
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>"SOLID STATE" GLOW PLUG SYSTEM REPLACEMENT PROCEDURES</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>During the course of troubleshooting the "Solid State" Glow Plug System if you find it necessary to
                replace the control unit, use the following procedure when replacing the control unit.
            </para>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="6">
            <title>Removal (Controller Assembly)</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the negative ground of the battery, Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4600622">6.22</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove air cleaner housing to expose the control unit module, Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4600623">6.23</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <figure id="ef4600622" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg10721" filename="../figcg1/cg10721.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 6.22 Disconnect Vehicle Battery</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4600623" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12476" filename="../figcg1/cg12476.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 6.23 Control Unit Module [1988 Model Year and before shown]</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove protective cover from control unit module. Squeeze the sides firmly and lift,
                    Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4600624">6.24</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <figure id="ef4600624" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg10723" filename="../figcg1/cg10723.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 6.24 Protective Cover Removal</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the following leads from the corresponding control unit terminals: (Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4600625">6.25</hotlnk>)
                </para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>Power lead (from battery)</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Main glow plug lead</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Ignition lead</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Ground</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
                <figure id="ef4600625" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg10724" filename="../figcg1/cg10724.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 6.25 Lead Disconnection for Control Unit Removal</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect wait light connector, Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4600626">6.26</hotlnk>. (Lift slotted retainer off tang and pull apart, Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4600626">6.26</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="ef4600626" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg10725" filename="../figcg1/cg10725.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 6.26 Disconnect Wait Light</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove control unit mounting bolts and hardened washers. Remove control unit module from
                    intake manifold, Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4600627">6.27</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <figure id="ef4600627" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg10726" filename="../figcg1/cg10726.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 6.27 Control Unit Mounting Bolts</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
